{"title_page": "Sech (singer)", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Panamanian singer}}\n{{Spanish name|Morales|Williams}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Sech\n| image            =\n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Carlos Isa\u00edas Morales Williams\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1993|12|03|mf=y}}\n| birth_place      = [[R\u00edo Abajo]], [[Ciudad de Panam\u00e1]], [[Panam\u00e1]]\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[Reggaeton]]|[[Latin R&B]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-latin/sech-otro-trago-feat-darell-ozuna-nicky-jam-anuel-aa-868525/|title=Song You Need to Know: Sech, 'Otro Trago (Remix)'|first1=Suzy|last1=Exposito|first2=Suzy|last2=Exposito|date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>}}\n| occupation       = Singer\n| instrument       = {{hlist|Vocals|piano}}\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| label            = Rich Music\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Justin Quiles]]|[[Ozuna]]}}\n}}\n'''Carlos Isa\u00edas Morales Williams''' (born December 3, 1993), better known as '''Sech''', is a Panamanian singer. In April 2019 he released his album ''Sue\u00f1os'', reaching number three on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Top Latin Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/latin-albums|title=Top Latin Albums|date=10 August 2019}}</ref> In an interview with ''Billboard'', Sech mentioned [[El General]] being an influence for his music.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roiz |first1=Jessica |title=Sech Reveals His Favorite Things About Panamanian Culture, Big Dreams in New 'Growing Up Latino' Episode |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8528580/sech-growing-up-latino-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=21 September 2019 |date=28 August 2019}}</ref> He first reached popularity with his song \"Miss Lonely\", in 2017.<ref name=\"Duality\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pollstar.com/article/hotstar-the-duality-of-sech-latin-americas-rising-urbano-star-142653|title=Hotstar: The Duality Of Sech, Latin America\u2019s Rising Urbano Star|website=www.pollstar.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n*''The Sensation'' (2018)\n*''Sue\u00f1os'' (2019)\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"8\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br><ref name=\"US\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/darell/chart-history/hot-100|title=Darell Chart History: Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Hot Latin Songs|US<br>Latin]]<br><ref name=\"USLatin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/darell/chart-history/latin-songs|title=Darell Chart History: Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 11, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Argentina Hot 100|ARG]]<br><ref name=\"ARG\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/sech/chart-history/ARG|title=Sech Chart History (Billboard Argentina Hot 100)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[National-Report|COL]]<br><ref name=\"COL\">Peak positions in Colombia:\n* \"Bebe\": {{cite web|url=http://www.national-report.com/top-colombia/|title=Top 100 Colombia \u2013 Semana 45 del 2018 \u2013 Del 02/11/2018 al 08/11/2018|publisher=[[National-Report]]|accessdate=February 8, 2019|language=Spanish|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115035647/http://www.national-report.com/top-colombia/|archivedate=November 15, 2018}}\n* \"Culpables\" and \"Adictiva\": {{cite web|url=http://www.national-report.com/top-colombia/|title=Top 100 Colombia \u2013 Semana 5 del 2019 \u2013 Del 25/01/2019 al 31/01/2019|publisher=[[National-Report]]|accessd