rd]]'' [[Top Latin Albums]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/latin-albums|title=Top Latin Albums|date=10 August 2019}}</ref> In an interview with ''Billboard'', Sech mentioned [[El General]] being an influence for his music.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roiz |first1=Jessica |title=Sech Reveals His Favorite Things About Panamanian Culture, Big Dreams in New 'Growing Up Latino' Episode |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/8528580/sech-growing-up-latino-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=21 September 2019 |date=28 August 2019}}</ref> He first reached popularity with his song \"Miss Lonely\", in 2017.<ref name=\"Duality\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pollstar.com/article/hotstar-the-duality-of-sech-latin-americas-rising-urbano-star-142653|title=Hotstar: The Duality Of Sech, Latin America\u2019s Rising Urbano Star|website=www.pollstar.com}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n=== Studio albums ===\n*''The Sensation'' (2018)\n*''Sue\u00f1os'' (2019)\n\n=== Singles ===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! colspan=\"8\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br><ref name=\"US\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/darell/chart-history/hot-100|title=Darell Chart History: Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=November 13, 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Hot Latin Songs|US<br>Latin]]<br><ref name=\"USLatin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/darell/chart-history/latin-songs|title=Darell Chart History: Hot Latin Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=January 11, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Argentina Hot 100|ARG]]<br><ref name=\"ARG\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/sech/chart-history/ARG|title=Sech Chart History (Billboard Argentina Hot 100)|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|